  "sections": [
    {
      "section_id": "doc_012_s01",
      "section_label": "body",
      "section_ordinal": 1,
      "paragraphs": [
        {
          "paragraph_id": "doc_012_s01_p01",
          "paragraph_ordinal": 1,
          "sentences": [
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_012_s01_p01_s01",
              "sentence_ordinal": 1,
              "text": "Executive Mansion, Washington, August 22, 1862.",
              "word_offset_start": 0,
              "word_offset_end": 6,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraph_id": "doc_012_s01_p02",
          "paragraph_ordinal": 2,
          "sentences": [
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_012_s01_p02_s01",
              "sentence_ordinal": 1,
              "text": "Hon. Horace Greeley: Dear Sir.",
              "word_offset_start": 6,
              "word_offset_end": 11,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraph_id": "doc_012_s01_p03",
          "paragraph_ordinal": 3,
          "sentences": [
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_012_s01_p03_s01",
              "sentence_ordinal": 1,
              "text": "I have just read yours of the 19th. addressed to myself through the New-York Tribune.",
              "word_offset_start": 11,
              "word_offset_end": 26,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_012_s01_p03_s02",
              "sentence_ordinal": 2,
              "text": "If there be in it any statements, or assumptions of fact, which I may know to be erroneous, I do not, now and here, controvert them.",
              "word_offset_start": 26,
              "word_offset_end": 52,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_012_s01_p03_s03",
              "sentence_ordinal": 3,
              "text": "If there be in it any inferences which I may believe to be falsely drawn, I do not now and here, argue against them.",
              "word_offset_start": 52,
              "word_offset_end": 76,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_012_s01_p03_s04",
              "sentence_ordinal": 4,
              "text": "If there be perceptable in it an impatient and dictatorial tone, I waive it in deference to an old friend, whose heart I have always supposed to be right.",
              "word_offset_start": 76,
              "word_offset_end": 105,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraph_id": "doc_012_s01_p04",
          "paragraph_ordinal": 4,
          "sentences": [
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_012_s01_p04_s01",
              "sentence_ordinal": 1,
              "text": "As to the policy I \"seem to be pursuing\" as you say, I have not meant to leave any one in doubt.",
              "word_offset_start": 105,
              "word_offset_end": 127,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraph_id": "doc_012_s01_p05",
          "paragraph_ordinal": 5,
          "sentences": [
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_012_s01_p05_s01",
              "sentence_ordinal": 1,
              "text": "I would save the Union.",
              "word_offset_start": 127,
              "word_offset_end": 132,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_012_s01_p05_s02",
              "sentence_ordinal": 2,
              "text": "I would save it the shortest way under the Constitution.",
              "word_offset_start": 132,
              "word_offset_end": 142,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_012_s01_p05_s03",
              "sentence_ordinal": 3,
              "text": "The sooner the national authority can be restored; the nearer the Union will be \"the Union as it was.\" If there be those who would not save the Union, unless they could at the same time save slavery, I do not agree with them.",
              "word_offset_start": 142,
              "word_offset_end": 186,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_012_s01_p05_s04",
              "sentence_ordinal": 4,
              "text": "If there be those who would not save the Union unless they could at the same time destroy slavery, I do not agree with them.",
              "word_offset_start": 186,
              "word_offset_end": 211,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_012_s01_p05_s05",
              "sentence_ordinal": 5,
              "text": "My paramount object in this struggle is to save the Union, and is not either to save or to destroy slavery.",
              "word_offset_start": 211,
              "word_offset_end": 232,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_012_s01_p05_s06",
              "sentence_ordinal": 6,
              "text": "If I could save the Union without freeing any slave I would do it, and if I could save it by freeing all the slaves I would do it; and if I could save it by freeing some and leaving others alone I would also do that.",
              "word_offset_start": 232,
              "word_offset_end": 279,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_012_s01_p05_s07",
              "sentence_ordinal": 7,
              "text": "What I do about slavery, and the colored race, I do because I believe it helps to save the Union; and what I forbear, I forbear because I do not believe it would help to save the Union.",
              "word_offset_start": 279,
              "word_offset_end": 317,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_012_s01_p05_s08",
              "sentence_ordinal": 8,
              "text": "I shall do less whenever I shall believe what I am doing hurts the cause, and I shall do more whenever I shall believe doing more will help the cause.",
              "word_offset_start": 317,
              "word_offset_end": 347,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_012_s01_p05_s09",
              "sentence_ordinal": 9,
              "text": "I shall try to correct errors when shown to be errors; and I shall adopt new views so fast as they shall appear to be true views.",
              "word_offset_start": 347,
              "word_offset_end": 374,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraph_id": "doc_012_s01_p06",
          "paragraph_ordinal": 6,
          "sentences": [
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_012_s01_p06_s01",
              "sentence_ordinal": 1,
              "text": "I have here stated my purpose according to my view of official duty; and I intend no modification of my oft-expressed personal wish that all men every where could be free.",
              "word_offset_start": 374,
              "word_offset_end": 405,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraph_id": "doc_012_s01_p07",
          "paragraph_ordinal": 7,
          "sentences": [
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_012_s01_p07_s01",
              "sentence_ordinal": 1,
              "text": "Yours, A. Lincoln.",
              "word_offset_start": 405,
              "word_offset_end": 408,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
